# EBWiki Project Rules for Perplexity Labs

## Project Context
EBWiki is a Rails 8.1.0 application using Ruby 3.4.2. It tracks cases of police brutality and provides a platform for community action.

## Critical Testing Requirements
- NEVER consider a task complete until all tests pass
- Always run `bundle exec rspec` or `rake spec` after making changes
- Test failures must be fixed before marking tasks as done
- Use `bundle exec rails server` to verify server starts without errors

## Environment Setup
Always use the ebwiki gemset for Ruby 3.4.2:
```
export GEM_HOME="/usr/share/rvm/gems/ruby-3.4.2@ebwiki"
export GEM_PATH="/usr/share/rvm/gems/ruby-3.4.2@ebwiki"
export PATH="${GEM_HOME}/bin:/usr/share/rvm/rubies/ruby-3.4.2/bin:/usr/share/rvm/bin:${PATH}"
```
Never include the global gemset in GEM_PATH unless explicitly needed. Keep PATH clean and non-redundant.

## Branch Naming Conventions
- Use `feature/` prefix for feature branches (e.g., `feature/playwright-integration`)
- For JIRA tickets: `feature/EB-N-description` format
- Keep branch names descriptive and kebab-case

## Ruby and Rails Version
- Current: Ruby 3.4.2, Rails 8.1.0
- Always maintain version consistency across:
  - `.ruby-version`
  - `Gemfile` ruby specification
  - `Dockerfile`
  - `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

## Testing Practices
- Run full test suite before claiming completion
- Playwright specs require headless browser setup
- WebMock must allow localhost connections for browser tests (js: true tagged specs)
- Use FactoryBot for test data creation
- DatabaseCleaner configured for test isolation

## Code Quality
- Fix all deprecation warnings
- Ensure Rubocop passes
- Maintain RSpec best practices (use `type: :feature` for feature specs)
- Don't create documentation until tests are confirmed passing

## Playwright/Browser Testing
- All Playwright specs use `js: true` tag
- WebMock automatically allows localhost for `js: true, type: :feature` specs
- Use `page.has_content?()` instead of `have_content()` for flexible matching
- Handle non-visible text gracefully (may be in title tags, etc.)

## Git Workflow
- Create separate PRs for distinct features/fixes
- Include comprehensive commit messages
- Link PRs to GitHub issues
- Request review from `gktreviewer` for significant changes

## Project-Specific Notes
- EBWiki uses Elasticsearch (may not be available in test environment - handle 500s gracefully)
- PaperTrail requires `PT_SILENCE_AR_COMPAT_WARNING=true` in test environment
- Bullet gem is temporarily commented out for Rails 8.1 compatibility
- Database uses PostgreSQL with full-text search capabilities

